==French==
#(grammar) [[past participle]] root verb suffix; translation ([[-ed]]);

-gender/tense/model verb altering a verb=bolded text
*French phrase build {masculine, sing.}: 
#P. build #1 {3rd masculine, sing.}:Il [avait]<--(glissé) [He had slipped]
#P. build #2 {3rd masculine, plur.}: Ils [avaient]<--(glissé) [They had slipped]
#P. build #3 {feminine, sing.}: '''Elle''' [était]<--(''glissée''''') [
'''Note:''' However, translations of French words ending in (-é) '''does not necessarily''' end in either of these English suffixes: ([[-y]]) ([[-ed]]).'' See ''[[past participle]]''.
*homophones: ([[et]]), ([[-er]]), ([[hé]])

